the dolan twins are one of the very few unproblematic youtubers. imagine having the strength to make this documentary and also make a fundraiser with all of this going on. losing someone so close to you is the worst pain in the world. and being able to handle all of the disgusting negative comments everyday while still trying to make others happy when you need it the most is something that is really hard, but they did it. i couldn't imagine being able to do all this while still missing my best friend.

Dear Ethan and Grayson,
i know you're probably not reading this, but just know - we will always be here for you no matter what. and your dad is watching above you, making sure you all are okay and you know that. he will always love you no matter if physically next to you or not. he is still alive in your hearts. i wish you guys all the best and just know we are really proud of you.

Yours sincerely,
the fandom <3

snippet.textDisplay: My grandad had cancer he was the strongest person I knew he was my best friend he helped me through everything he passed away on 2nd of December 2018. The last time I saw him he was confused he didn't know what we going on i got home that night I was so upset I didn't want to see him in so much pain. The night before he passed away i was so upset we didn't know how long he had left but we knew it wasn't long my mam came into me and asked what I was i just cried into her arms she told me everything was going to be okay . My step dad woke me up the next day and said to pack my bags I had to go to my home town because grandad wasnt doing well then half an hour later my step dad asked me to go into the sitting room my sister was in there and so was my step dad's mother my sister was crying so much and I knew what it was it didn't feel right . I got to my home town and when I saw my mam I cried my eyes out I didn't want it till be real then I saw him my best friend wasn't breathing my auntie was there me and my sister were so upset we were with him everyday he made us breakfast and lunch and dinner everyday since my mam was working so much it was so hard to see him like that. This documentary really helped me since I haven't been able to come to terms of the fact he passed away so thank you so much for making this it helped me so much and I'm sure it helped other people just as much as me. I'm so sorry for your passing I know how you feel it's so hard and it's never going to be the same. Stay strong he'd want you to be happy and think of the good times with him when he was his happiest. Thank you

snippet.textDisplay: I literally just lost a family member that means the world to me more than anyone I had ever known In my entire life just a couple of weeks ago, and I have been going through a really rough time especially processing my emotions and how to deal with the grief. For the past week  this video has been popping up in my feed every-time I open YouTube and I would scroll past it so fast because I wasn’t ready to deal with anything that might trigger something in me. But I kept seeing it over and over every time I open the YouTube app. I’m not subscribed to your channel nor  am I a fan of yours but I can’t explain how important this has been and how much clarity it has given me with my own emotions and journey. I am so sorry for your loss and I genuinely feel your pain and you both are lucky to be in a family where you can sit around like that and talk about your thoughts and emotions. Always keep that in mind and good luck to those who are going through something like this alone , unable to share any of it. I hope time will make the pain easier to deal with.. cause I know that it’ll never go away.

snippet.textDisplay:
Cuz.
I've met a few people in life whose fathers had passed on...
And I remember the stories of how amazing and awesome these men were as dad and husbands. The love given to them reaching BEYOND this side of existence. White dude I know, his dad died 24 YEARS AGO. Talks about the guy like he was comin over to hang out later. Meanwhile, MY dad and I arent even on SPEAKING terms.
I'm TRULY envious of these guys. I mean that in a GOOD way. If there is one.
To be BLESSED to be the son of a cool dad.
The impact of that is a positive FORCE that'll affect people in ways you wont think.
A kid in elementary school had one of those cool dads. The whole class wanted to be that kid.
And because of what I've seen in life.
I'M one of those cool dads.
PARADISE in PEACE to your father.
